Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and put your #kettle{} on to boil. Trim the
@courgette{1} and quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small chunks. Halve
the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.
Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot,
add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g}, @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}, red
pepper, @dried oregano{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Brown the
chicken on all sides, about ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, in a #measuring jug{},
dissolve the @chicken stock powder{1} in the @water{75%ml}. Put a large
#saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Pour the chicken stock and @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2}(tin)
into the pan with the chicken and bacon. Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g} and
courgette. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium until the mixture
is simmering away. Cook until the sauce is thick and tomatoey and the veggies
are soft, stirring occasionally, about ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook
until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{}
and return to the pan. Mix in the @creme fraiche{99%g} and season with salt
and pepper.

Add half the parsley to the chicken and veggies and stir through. Transfer the
mixture to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the creamy pasta. Cover with the
@hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and pop on the top shelf of your
oven. Bake until the top is golden and a little crunchy at the edges,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Serve the chicken and bacon pasta bake in #bowls{} and finish with a
sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've decided to add bacon to your meal. Add it to the pan
> when you add the chicken, pepper and dried oregano. Continue with the step
> and the rest of the recipe as instructed.